# IDE / clangd helpers
# compile_commands.json is mirrored at the project root by the top-level
# CMakeLists.txt after every build so clangd / IDEs can find it without
# configuration. The canonical copy lives in the build dir and travels
# with `cmake -B ...`, so the project-root mirror is purely a
# per-machine convenience.
compile_commands.json
# clangd writes its on-disk index here when it consumes the
# compile_commands.json above. Per-checkout, never committed.
.cache/
